This project entails the creation of a 10000mAh power bank, which is made up of two separate modules: a battery charging module and a booster module. 
To carry out their primary functions, each of these modules contains a distinct circuit. 
The portable device is made up of four Li-ion batteries, each rated at 3.7V and 2600mAh, that are connected in parallel. 
The battery charging module is in charge of controlling the current flow to the batteries as well as charging overflow.
In this protable device an extra feature of emergency light is built in the ine side of the Portable device
